tables.description: The audit_checks table represents a record of regular checks performed on various sites to ensure compliance and adherence to standards. It stores information about the date of the check, the site being checked, and the auditor who performed the check. This table is typically used in analytics and business workflows to track the effectiveness of the audit process and identify areas for improvement.

columns.description: The audit_pk column represents a unique identifier for each audit check record, allowing for efficient retrieval and updating of individual records. It stores an integer value and is used as the primary key for the audit_checks table.

The site_fk column links each audit check record to the corresponding site in the site_master table, enabling the tracking of site-specific audit data. It stores an integer value referencing the site_pk in the site_master table.

The audit_dt column captures the date of each audit check, providing a timestamp for when the check was performed. It stores a date value and is used to track the frequency and timing of audit checks.

The auditor column stores the name of the person who performed the audit check, allowing for accountability and tracking of audit personnel. It stores a character varying value and is used to identify the auditor responsible for each record.

The audit_score column represents the result of the audit check, indicating the level of compliance or adherence to standards. It stores an integer value and is used to evaluate the effectiveness of the audit process.

tables.description: The event_log table stores a record of events that occur within the organization, including staff activities, system updates, and other notable occurrences. It captures information about the event category, risk level, and the staff member involved. This table is crucial for auditing, troubleshooting, and understanding the organization's operational history.

columns.description: The event_pk column serves as a unique identifier for each event log record, enabling efficient retrieval and updating of individual records. It stores an integer value and is used as the primary key for the event_log table.

The staff_fk column links each event log record to the corresponding staff member in the staff table, allowing for tracking of staff activities and events. It stores an integer value referencing the staff_pk in the staff table.
The event_dt column captures the date of each event, providing a timestamp for when the event occurred. It stores a date value and is used to track the frequency and timing of events.
The event_category column stores the type or category of the event, enabling classification and analysis of event data. It stores a character varying value and is used to identify the type of event.

The risk_level column represents the level of risk associated with each event, indicating the potential impact or consequences of the event. It stores an integer value and is used to evaluate the severity of events.

tables.description: The learning_records table tracks the training and development activities of staff members, including the courses they have completed, the dates of completion, and their current completion status. This table is essential for HR and talent development teams to monitor staff growth, identify knowledge gaps, and plan future training initiatives.

columns.description: The learning_pk column serves as a unique identifier for each learning record, enabling efficient retrieval and updating of individual records. It stores an integer value and is used as the primary key for the learning_records table.

The staff_fk column links each learning record to the corresponding staff member in the staff table, allowing for tracking of staff learning activities. It stores an integer value referencing the staff_pk in the staff table.

The course_name column stores the name of the course or training program completed by the staff member, enabling tracking of learning activities and course completion. It stores a character varying value and is used to identify the course.

The course_dt column captures the date of course completion, providing a timestamp for when the course was finished. It stores a date value and is used to track the frequency and timing of course completion.

The completion_status column represents the status of course completion, indicating whether the course was completed or not. It stores a character varying value and is used to evaluate the effectiveness of learning programs.

tables.description: The org_units table represents the organizational structure of the company, including departments, teams, and other units. It stores information about the unit title, site affiliation, unit head, and creation date. This table is vital for understanding the company's hierarchy, identifying key personnel, and making informed organizational decisions.

columns.description: The unit_pk column serves as a unique identifier for each organizational unit, enabling efficient retrieval and updating of individual records. It stores an integer value and is used as the primary key for the org_units table.
The unit_title column stores the title or name of the organizational unit, enabling identification and classification of units. It stores a character varying value and is used to identify the unit.

The site_fk column links each organizational unit to the corresponding site in the site_master table, enabling tracking of site-specific unit data. It stores an integer value referencing the site_pk in the site_master table.

The unit_head column stores the name of the person responsible for the organizational unit, enabling identification of key personnel. It stores a character varying value and is used to identify the unit head.

The created_on column captures the date and time when the organizational unit was created, providing a timestamp for when the unit was established. It stores a timestamp without time zone value and is used to track the creation date of units.

tables.description: The site_master table contains information about the company's sites, including their titles, locations, and creation dates. It provides a comprehensive view of the company's global presence and is used to track site-related data, such as site performance, customer interactions, and operational metrics.

columns.description: The site_pk column serves as a unique identifier for each site, enabling efficient retrieval and updating of individual records. It stores an integer value and is used as the primary key for the site_master table.
The site_title column stores the title or name of the site, enabling identification and classification of sites. It stores a character varying value and is used to identify the site.

The nation column stores the country or nation where the site is located, enabling tracking of site locations and geographical data. It stores a character varying value and is used to identify the site's location.

The region column stores the region or area where the site is located, enabling tracking of site locations and geographical data. It stores a character varying value and is used to identify the site's location.

The created_on column captures the date and time when the site was created, providing a timestamp for when the site was established. It stores a timestamp without time zone value and is used to track the creation date of sites.

tables.description: The staff table stores information about the company's employees, including their full names, unit affiliations, roles, and joining dates. This table is essential for HR, payroll, and talent management teams to manage staff data, track employee movements, and make informed personnel decisions.

columns.description: The staff_pk column serves as a unique identifier for each staff member, enabling efficient retrieval and updating of individual records. It stores an integer value and is used as the primary key for the staff table.
The staff_fullname column stores the full name of the staff member, enabling identification and classification of staff. It stores a character varying value and is used to identify the staff member.

The unit_fk column links each staff member to the corresponding organizational unit in the org_units table, enabling tracking of staff unit affiliations. It stores an integer value referencing the unit_pk in the org_units table.

The role_name column stores the role or position of the staff member, enabling identification and classification of staff roles. It stores a character varying value and is used to identify the staff member's role.

The joining_date column captures the date when the staff member joined the organization, providing a timestamp for when the staff member was hired. It stores a date value and is used to track the joining date of staff members.
